post_text:
Thanks to a new USDA program, we will be offering free breakfast and free lunches to ALL of our USD 332 enrolled students. This will not include any extra milks such as for snacks, sack lunches, Kindergarten milk, etc. This program will take effect today, September 8th and is set to expire December 31, 2020, or until the USDA funding runs out.

Families do not need to apply for the free meal program. Any current lunch money on the student's accounts will be held for use after the free meal program expires. Students will be asked to report if they are planning to eat breakfast for the following day.

Thank you to USDA for making this possible!

Cunningham Bridges to Learning:
Interested in Preschool for the 2020/21 school year?

There will be NO in person screenings scheduled. If you are interested in preschool for the 2020/21 school year then you must complete this new screening process.

1) Call (620-672-7500) or e-mail
Sandra (sandra.espino@scksec.com)
2) Complete screening forms and send back
3) You will receive a call to go over screening results
4) Once this process is complete they will forward us your contact info and you will be added to our list.

Spots are not guaranteed, but we try hard to place as many interested students as possible.

Please PM us if you have any questions!!

If your child is currently enrolled in preschool THIS past school year you do NOT have to complete this screening. You will be placed on a class list automatically. This is only for NEW incoming students.

"Have you ever seen a Rube Goldberg machine in action? You probably have, even if you didn't know what it was. A Rube Goldberg machine is a contraption that uses a chain reaction to carry out a simple task. It performs a very basic job in a complicated way." (wonderopolis.org)
The Physical Science students were challenged to build such a machine for part of their class requirements. The students had to include at least 3 simple machines and 2 energy transfers. I am really proud of these students for all of their hard work! More machines will be coming in the future!

shared_text:
Randy Watson
March 15 at 4:33 PM ¬∑

As of Sunday, March 15, Kansas Education Commissioner Dr. Randy Watson strongly recommends that those schools currently coming off of spring break, suspend operations for the week March 16-20. All schools scheduled for spring break the week of March 16-20 will continue as planned. For schools who have spring break later in time, Commissioner Watson is strongly recommending they also close schools for the period of March 16-20.

Closing all schools during this same period of time provides Kansas officials the time needed to finalize a comprehensive plan for how to address COVID-19.

It is critical that we all follow a coordinated response to this situation.

post_text:
Attention PowerSchool Parents

PowerSchool parents that have a parent login. There is an option to receive email updates regarding your students grades, attendance and balance. The emails were not working...but we were able to fix it on Friday. With that you may have received several emails early this morning. You can log in and check your settings regarding what alerts you want to modify the number of emails you receive.

We've learned a better option to receive this info is through the actual PowerSchool App. If you download the app (from your app store search "PowerSchool") and login that way, it will:

1) keep you logged in so you don't have to keep logging in and attempt to remember your username and password
2) send you notifications for grade changes etc vs an email
3) be much easier to navigate and get what you want

Once you have the PowerSchool app downloaded you will use the same login you've already created and the school code "FSGT".

As always, if you need any help or are struggling at all please call the office and we will get you setup. 620-298-2473

Thank you!
text:
Attention PowerSchool Parents

PowerSchool parents that have a parent login. There is an option to receive email updates regarding your students grades, attendance and balance. The emails were not working...but we were able to fix it on Friday. With that you may have received several emails early this morning. You can log in and check your settings regarding what alerts you want to modify the number of emails you receive.

We've learned a better option to receive this info is through the actual PowerSchool App. If you download the app (from your app store search "PowerSchool") and login that way, it will:

1) keep you logged in so you don't have to keep logging in and attempt to remember your username and password
2) send you notifications for grade changes etc vs an email
3) be much easier to navigate and get what you want

Once you have the PowerSchool app downloaded you will use the same login you've already created and the school code "FSGT".

As always, if you need any help or are struggling at all please call the office and we will get you setup. 620-298-2473

Thank you!
